-- DEBUG: Tests that use debug mode to verify structural parsing
-- These tests verify behavior that cannot be tested via normal round-trip:
-- - Whitespace sensitivity (space placement changes semantics)
-- - Column sensitivity (poem/heir behavior depends on columns)
-- - String content extraction (verify escape handling produces correct content)

---- STRING CONTENT EXTRACTION -----------------------------------------------
-- These verify that string literals extract to the correct content

=== escaped quotes in string | 80 | debug
"He said ""Hello"""
---
' He said "Hello"

=== span strips content | 80 | debug
'''hello'''
---
' hello

=== span with quotes extracts quotes | 80 | debug
'''say "hello"'''
---
' say "hello"

=== span multiline strips indent | 80 | debug
'''line one
   line two'''
---
' line one
' line two

=== page strips content | 80 | debug
'''
hello
'''
---
' hello

=== page multiline joins lines | 80 | debug
'''
line one
line two
'''
---
' line one
' line two

---- WHITESPACE SENSITIVITY --------------------------------------------------
-- Space placement determines whether runes are prefix or infix

=== 3 +4 is prefix clump | 80 | debug
3 +4
---
«3 ‹+4›»

=== 3+ 4 is infix | 80 | debug
3+ 4
---
«3 + 4»

=== clumped runes not infix | 80 | debug
(a ,b +c)
---
(a ‹,b› ‹+c›)

---- COLUMN SENSITIVITY ------------------------------------------------------
-- Poem and heir behavior depends on column positions

=== poem: same col stays inside | 80 | debug
+ a
b
---
⟨⟨+ a⟩
 b⟩

=== poem heir | 80 | debug
+ a
+ b
---
⟨⟨+ a⟩
 ⟨+ b⟩⟩

=== poem heir with children | 80 | debug
+ a
+ b
  c
---
⟨⟨+ a⟩
 ⟨+ b c⟩⟩

=== poem in parens, low col | 80 | debug
(+ a
b)
---
(   ⟨+ a⟩
 b)

=== block: poem eats items | 80 | debug
f =
  + a
  b
  c
---
⟦f =⟧
    ⟨⟨+ a⟩
     b
     c⟩

---- STRUCTURE VERIFICATION --------------------------------------------------
-- Tests that verify specific parsing rules

=== two runes don't trigger block | 80 | debug
a + b =
  x
---
««a + b» = x»

=== trailing rune after slot | 80 | debug
(a b , 4 +)
---
(«a b» , «4 +»)

